cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper deals with the application of deep learning algorithms to neuroimaging data, specifically 3D structural MRI brain scans, for classification of Alzheimer's disease. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of deep learning algorithms for automatic feature generation and analysis also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques for data preprocessing, which could potentially fall under the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
